.TH "tb_switch_suspend" 9 "tb_switch_suspend" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_switch_suspend \- Put a switch to sleep
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tb_switch_suspend
.BI "(struct tb_switch *sw "  ","
.BI "bool runtime "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sw" 12
Switch to suspend
.IP "runtime" 12
Is this runtime suspend or system sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Suspends router and all its children. Enables wakes according to
value of \fIruntime\fP and then sets sleep bit for the router. If \fIsw\fP is
host router the domain is ready to go to sleep once this function
returns.
